reviewText: Amusing pair of East Side Kids antics.  The first, Ghosts on the Loose, is about the Kids trying to fix up a house for a friend who just married and running into weird goings-on.  The second, Spooks Run Wild, is the better of the two about the Kids ending up at an apparently haunted house with secret passages, walking suits of armor, and Bela Lugosi.  The best part is when they scare the bejabbers out of Lugosi.  The quality of both films is pretty good.  Recommended.
summary: East Side Kids Double Feature: Ghosts on the Loose & Spooks Run Wild

reviewText: For those of you not familiar with The East Side Kids, these are two excellent movies to begin with.  The East Side Kids, led by Leo Gorcey and Bobby Jordan, are a group of teens always getting into trouble.  In the first movie, they find a nazi spy headquarters in a 'haunted' house.  In the second, they are off in the country in a camp for troubled teens and end up in another haunted house with a murderer.  Bela Lugosi plays a small part in the first film and a more integral part in the second.  Each film is just over an hour in length.  So grab a cup of hot chocolate, curl up on the couch and enjoy these great classic films!
summary: The East Side Kids at their best!

reviewText: Very pleased with Ghosts on the Loose.  It's a very good quality print with all original titles and no splices. Unfortunately, Spooks Run Wild was a disappointment.  It has a problem playing well on some players.  Besides being a re-issue print, when originals are easily available, it was quite jumpy.  It appeared to me to a combination of a lesser print and poor dvd production.
